    Sit in History and Savor It All
    On our visit to Barcelona we knew the Placa Reial was on the list of must see places. After a full morning of Goudi and scenic views of the city from every corner, we just happened to stumble into the Placa Reial. Easy check mark and such fun! We were able to get a table at one venue for lunch right on the square, and another great seat from a different vantage point for dinner and had great meals while being entertained by the various street performers who do their show for the hopes of a Euro or two (or more) by the viewers. So much activity and fun just to watch the people as you take in the history of your location and all that has happened in this incredible space. Recommend you bring coins for the performers and space on your camera for the many pictures you will want to take. Also, a good size appetite for the many, many good options all around the square to eat and sip through the afternoon and into the night!
    Visited June 2024
